"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The activation map, in the right anterior oblique projection, was obtained by electroanatomic mapping during atrial tachycardia. The earliest activation, shown in red (arrow), represents the origin of the tachycardia located in the posterolateral right atrium in the region of the crista terminalis. The impulse spreads from this focus (yellow to green to blue), to activate the rest of the right atrium. The last part to be activated is the region around the superior vena cave (SVC) (deep blue).",
